The paper deals with using KG embeddings to answer logical queries, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces two new datasets for evaluation, which suggests a focus on database-related research (cs.DB). The use of attention mechanisms and neural networks for query answering also suggests a potential fit for natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques for querying incomplete KGs, which could also fit under the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
